      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 167: filterDisallowedLinks(in:) only clears `.link` and underline for rejected markdown links, but it leaves any foreground color/font/style produced by the Markdown parser. A message like `[text](javascript:alert(1))` will no longer open the URL, but can still look like an active link, which is misleading and creates a phishing-style UX issue. Clear all link styling for rejected links, or convert rejected markdown links to plain label text before parsing. For example:\n```suggestion\nattributed[run.range].link \u003d nil\nattributed[run.range].foregroundColor \u003d nil\nattributed[run.range].underlineStyle \u003d nil\n```",
