      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 206: stripMarkdownLinks(in:) mutates `result` while using ranges computed from the original `text`. Swift `String.Index` values are invalidated by mutation and are not guaranteed to remain valid for another String instance after replacement; multiple markdown links can therefore trap or replace the wrong span. Recompute the label and replacement range against `result` before each mutation, or perform replacements using NSRange offsets from the end. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nstatic func stripMarkdownLinks(in text: String) -\u003e String {\n    var result \u003d text\n    for originalRange in markdownLinkRanges(in: text).reversed() {\n        let lowerOffset \u003d text.distance(from: text.startIndex, to: originalRange.lowerBound)\n        let upperOffset \u003d text.distance(from: text.startIndex, to: originalRange.upperBound)\n        let lower \u003d result.index(result.startIndex, offsetBy: lowerOffset)\n        let upper \u003d result.index(result.startIndex, offsetBy: upperOffset)\n        let range \u003d lower..\u003cupper\n\n        guard let openBracket \u003d result[range].firstIndex(of: \"[\"),\n              let closeBracket \u003d result[range].firstIndex(of: \"]\") else { continue }\n        let labelStart \u003d result.index(after: openBracket)\n        result.replaceSubrange(range, with: String(result[labelStart..\u003ccloseBracket]))\n    }\n    return result\n}\n```",
